This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL) as it deals with generative modeling of text and discrimination between real and machine-generated text. Additionally, it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves training a scoring function to discriminate between real and fake text. The Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper mentions the use of neural networks for text generation. Finally, the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category could also be relevant as the paper discusses the use of discriminative models for image captioning.
